news.title: Brookfield subsidiary defaults on two Los Angeles office buildings
news.para: The two properties, part of Brookfield DTLA Fund Office Trust Investor's portfolio, are 777 Tower and Gas Company Tower, with debts around $290 million and $465 million, respectively.

news.title: MYRE Capital to raise Rs 20 crore through structured debt
news.para: Myre Capital is in the process to apply for the Securities and Exchange Board of India's (SEBI) online bond platform (OBPs) measures.

news.title: Officials inspect Porvorim land for bypass, find it full of buildings
news.para: To ensure there’s no traffic congestion while this road is being built, the government constituted a team comprising representatives of various departments including PWD, panchayats, town and country planning, and land survey, apart from the Goa police’s traffic cell.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: Rs 3 lakh crore offers bagged at GIS, hunt now for land to execute them
news.para: Over the next five years – during which the investments would be made – land would be pooled or acquired mostly in areas off the Yamuna Expressway and the Dadri-Noida-Ghaziabad Investment Region (DNGIR).

news.title: Sebi notifies governance norms for REITs, InvITs similar to listed companies
news.para: This comes after the board of Sebi approved a proposal in December for introducing governance norms for REITs and InvITs on the lines of corporate governance norms for listed companies.

news.title: Residents of Aurangabad's fringe areas forced to assess own properties for tax
news.para: With the local civic body allegedly shying away from its responsibility of bringing the properties under the tax net, a section of citizens claimed that they are now taking help of agents for evaluation of property tax.

news.title: Mumbai's MMRDA to get 91 lakh sq ft saleable area after metro-I takeover: RTI
news.para: MMRDA has a 26% stake in the special purpose vehicle - MMOPL, which runs the Metro I - while Anil Ambani-owned Reliance Infrastructure holds 74%. The 12km corridor between Versova-Andheri-Ghatkopar has 12 stations and a depot at DN Nagar.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 599 properties over property tax default
news.para: The tax and revenue department sealed a total of 2,358 properties in the last one week for defaulting on payment of tax despite repeated notices, a statement from the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation said.

news.title: Adani Group looks to repay $500 million bridge loan to fund acquisition of Holcim cement units
news.para: The bridge loan has a tenor of six months and was part of the larger financing package of $5.25 billion, which included a $3 billion senior debt with a tenor of 18 months, a $1 billion mezzanine facility with tenor of 24 months and a $750 million loan against shares.

news.title: Indore civic body to crackdown on illegal colonies from February 15
news.para: IMC commissioner Pratibha Pal on Tuesday reviewed the status of works related to the colony cell and instructed officials to launch a crackdown against illegal colonies to remove illegal structures as part of its anti-encroachment drive.

news.title: Stilt plus four floor buildings cannot be constructed in Panchkula: Haryana government
news.para: When asked if such a ban would be applicable on Panchkula or the entire state, Gian Chand Gupta, speaker, Haryana assembly said it is for Panchkula city only. He, however, added a formal order mentioning all conditions and area of operation may be released within two days.

news.title: Mehrauli demolition: Delhi HC orders authorities to maintain status quo till Feb 16
news.para: ​The high court also asked the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) to state its stand on a batch of petitions challenging the demolition action and seeking a bar on demolition in the Mehrauli Archaeological Park area in south Delhi till a fresh "demarcation report" has been prepared.

news.title: Axis-Tishman Speyer's commercial realty platform secures Rs 400 crore first close
news.para: Through this first-ever alliance in the country between a fund house and an international real estate major, Axis Asset Management Co is raising up to '1,500 crore including a green-shoe option, while Tishman Speyer will act as the exclusive development manager for the platform.

news.title: Gurugram: Two more towers in Chintels Paradiso declared unsafe
news.para: ​Towers E and F of the society in Sector 109 are not fit for habitation, Additional Deputy Commissioner (ADC) Vishram Kumar Meena said, adding that the IIT-Delhi team completed the sampling work of towers A and G while the same for Tower H is in progress.

news.title: No 'coercive action' till March 15 against DLF: Allahabad HC
news.para: Following a Supreme Court order of May last year, the Authority had on December 1 handed Rs 295 crore to Reddy Veerana, who owned 7,400sqm in Chhalera Bangar village.
